The graph below best illustrates which of the following? <image 1>

A. The spacing effect
B. The impact of elaborative rehearsal on recall
C. Hermann Ebbinghaus's forgetting curve
D. The effect of visual imagery on retention
E. The serial position effect

The graph best illustrates the impact of elaborative rehearsal on recall. The shaded area represents the intermediate recall level, which is higher than the primacy and lower than the recency recall levels. This suggests that elaborative rehearsal can improve recall, as evidenced by the higher intermediate recall compared to the primacy and recency recall levels. Therefore, the correct answer is B.
